docs.abstract: A Black superintendent’s email to parents after the killing of George Floyd engulfed a small, predominantly white Maryland community in a yearlong firestorm.
docs.snippet: A Black superintendent’s email to parents after the killing of George Floyd engulfed a small, predominantly white Maryland community in a yearlong firestorm.
docs.lead_paragraph: CENTREVILLE, Md. — When Andrea Kane sat down to write a letter to parents in her school district days after George Floyd’s death in 2020, images of the Black man pleading for his life under the knee of a white Minnesota police officer were haunting her.

headline.main: Black Lives Matter, She Wrote. Then ‘Everything Just Imploded.’
headline.print_headline: After Note on Racism, School District ‘Imploded’

docs.abstract: The things that are driving us apart are going to keep driving us apart.
docs.snippet: The things that are driving us apart are going to keep driving us apart.
docs.lead_paragraph: There has been a remarkable erosion in public tolerance of “offensive expression about race, gender and religion,” according to a paper Dennis Chong and Morris Levy, political scientists at the University of Southern California, and Jack Citrin, a political scientist at Berkeley, presented in September at the annual meeting of the American Political Science Association.

headline.main: The Moral Chasm That Has Opened Up Between Left and Right Is Widening

docs.abstract: Killings of Arabs by Arabs have soared in Israel. The prevailing assumption, an official said, was “as long as they are killing each other, that’s their problem.”
docs.snippet: Killings of Arabs by Arabs have soared in Israel. The prevailing assumption, an official said, was “as long as they are killing each other, that’s their problem.”
docs.lead_paragraph: TAIBEH, Israel — After a day of work in construction, Alaa Sarsour, 25, showered, dressed and walked the short distance to his friend’s pre-wedding henna party in a cobbled alley festooned with ribbons in the old heart of Taibeh, an Arab town in central Israel.

headline.main: Violent Crime Spikes Among Arabs in Israel as Officials Admit Neglect
headline.print_headline: Killings Among Arabs Soar in Israel, Baring Its Neglect of Crime

docs.abstract: His slur-filled comments are just the tip of the iceberg when it comes to the culture of the N.F.L.
docs.snippet: His slur-filled comments are just the tip of the iceberg when it comes to the culture of the N.F.L.
docs.lead_paragraph: In emails written between 2011 and 2018, Jon Gruden, then an ESPN analyst and past and future N.F.L. head coach, said that the leader of the N.F.L. players’ union, who is Black, had “lips the size of Michelin tires,” and used homophobic and misogynist language to denigrate people in football including Roger Goodell, the N.F.L. commissioner. It says a lot about the culture of football that it took years for these emails to come to light. The emails shocked me, but when I look at the bigger picture, I realize they shouldn’t have.

headline.main: Jon Gruden’s Emails Shocked Me. They Shouldn’t Have.

docs.abstract: Civic boosters in central Montana hoped for some federal money to promote tourism. A disinformation campaign got in the way.
docs.snippet: Civic boosters in central Montana hoped for some federal money to promote tourism. A disinformation campaign got in the way.
docs.lead_paragraph: GREAT FALLS, Mont. — In the summer of 2020, as pandemic shutdowns closed businesses and racial justice protests erupted on American streets, Rae Grulkowski, a 56-year-old businesswoman who had never been involved in politics but was alarmed about what was happening to the country, found a way to make a difference.

headline.main: Where Facts Were No Match for Fear
headline.print_headline: Falsehoods Meddle in Humble Bid to Honor Past

docs.abstract: “What really happened on that day?” Gwen Carr, Eric Garner’s mother, asked about her son’s death on Staten Island seven years ago.
docs.snippet: “What really happened on that day?” Gwen Carr, Eric Garner’s mother, asked about her son’s death on Staten Island seven years ago.
docs.lead_paragraph: The anguished pleas of Eric Garner as he struggled in a New York City police officer’s chokehold in 2014 galvanized millions, and his last words — “I can’t breathe,” repeated 11 times and captured on video — became a rallying cry for a protest movement demanding that police officers be held accountable.

headline.main: Officers to Testify About Eric Garner’s Death in Long-Delayed Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Police Officers to Testify  About Chokehold Death  In Long-Delayed Inquiry

docs.abstract: This Netflix documentary, filmed in different countries throughout 2020, is grueling to watch.
docs.snippet: This Netflix documentary, filmed in different countries throughout 2020, is grueling to watch.
docs.lead_paragraph: A sweeping chronicle of the global fight against the coronavirus, “Convergence: Courage in a Crisis,” directed by Orlando von Einsiedel, feels too much like we’re sitting down to watch the pandemic unfold all over again.

headline.main: ‘Convergence: Courage in a Crisis’ Review: Tracing a Pandemic’s Arc
